<unit xmlns="Unit"
      xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
      unitid="Illu_SubSequence"
      xsi:schemaLocation="Unit file:/C:/xampp/htdocs/moodle/mod/msm/NewSchemas/Unit.xsd">
   <titles>
      <title>Subsequence: Illustration</title>
   </titles>
   <body>
      <block>
         <block.body>
            <para>
               <para.body>Given a sequence <math>
                     <latex>(a_n)</latex>
                  </math> of real numbers, we obtain a subsequence by forming a composite</para.body>
            </para>
            <math.display>
               <latex>\NNr \overset{n}{\longrightarrow} \NNr \overset{a}{\longrightarrow} \RNr</latex>
            </math.display>
            <para>
               <para.body>Thus we obtain a new sequence <math>
                     <latex>(b_i)</latex>
                  </math> of real numbers, with</para.body>
            </para>
            <math.display>
               <latex>b_0:=a_{n(0)}=:a_{n_0},\quad b_1:=a_{n(1)}=:a_{n_1},\quad b_2:=b_{n(2)}=:a_{n_2},\quad \dots</latex>
            </math.display>
            <para>
               <para.body>In the graphic below this process gives</para.body>
            </para>
            <media type="image" active="0" inline="0">
               <img xmlns="" src="ims/SubSequence.png"/>
            </media>
            <ol>
               <li>
                  <para>
                     <para.body>
                        <math>
                           <latex>b_0 = a_{n_0} = a_3</latex>
                        </math>
                     </para.body>
                  </para>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <para>
                     <para.body>
                        <math>
                           <latex>b_1 = a_{n_1} = a_4</latex>
                        </math>
                     </para.body>
                  </para>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <para>
                     <para.body>
                        <math>
                           <latex>b_2 = a_{n_2} = a_7</latex>
                        </math>
                     </para.body>
                  </para>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <para>
                     <para.body>etc.</para.body>
                  </para>
               </li>
            </ol>
         </block.body>
      </block>
      <block>
         <block.body>
            <para>
               <para.body>Thus we may think of a subsequence of <math>
                     <latex>(a_n)</latex>
                  </math> as the outcome of</para.body>
            </para>
            <ol>
               <li>
                  <para>
                     <para.body>Omitting some members of the original sequence</para.body>
                  </para>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <para>
                     <para.body>Re-indexing the remaining sequence elements, as described above.</para.body>
                  </para>
               </li>
            </ol>
         </block.body>
      </block>
   </body>
</unit>